settings.content: I fell in love with this keyboard at first sight — the black and pink combo looks amazing! Plus, it has a knob that lets you control both the RGB lighting and the volume. Super convenient!

The AULA 108 Pro feels amazing to type on and use overall.
That knob and built-in screen? Easily one of the best features you can get on a keyboard right now.
You can even customize what info shows up on the screen — super handy.
The keyboard also has a really solid build. It’s heavy in a good way and feels premium.

This is my new keyboard — and honestly, it’s amazing.
It holds up so well against my old $300 Razer keyboard.
Didn’t expect that at all!

I switched both my keyboard and mouse to AULA — they’re compact, cool, and totally worth the price.
My friend came over for a BBQ and literally tried to walk off with my keyboard. 😭😂

Keycaps with side lighting and side-printed legends are just so cool.
I mean, no one stares straight down at their keyboard while typing anyway.
I’m really happy with this one — super satisfied!

I bought two AULA 75 keyboards — one for me and one for my girlfriend.
We both love them! AULA really gives you great value for the price.
I actually got one of their mice last time too, and it was awesome as well.
Safe to say — we’re big AULA fans now.

This keyboard was actually recommended by a friend. I hadn’t used any AULA products before, but now that I’ve been using it for three weeks, I can honestly say — whether it’s for gaming or just chatting, it’s the best keyboard I’ve tried under $100. I’m definitely an AULA fan now.

“Seriously cool! Great for folks who don’t need labels. That purple frame on top? Total personality and feels solid — not cheap at all. Love it at first sight. I’ve already been bragging to my friends about my newest desk addition!”

I found out about this keyboard from one of my favorite YouTubers — he highly recommended it.
He mentioned that buying from the official website gives you a longer warranty, which is cool.
But honestly, I don’t think I’ll even need the warranty — the build quality feels super solid.
I’ve been using it for a week now and it’s been great so far!
